# addy-osmani-skills — Cursor Rules

Personal tribute site publishing Addy Osmani's agent-skills as a browsable docs site. Not official, not Anthropic-affiliated.

## Stack (locked)

- **Bun** (runtime + package manager)
- **Astro** (static output, Vercel adapter) + **TypeScript strict**
- **Biome** — only lint/format tool (no ESLint, no Prettier)
- **Vitest** (unit) + **Playwright** (e2e)
- **Plain CSS** with design tokens — no Tailwind, no CSS-in-JS, no UI kits

## Astro patterns

- `.astro` components for all static surfaces
- Client islands only for interactive UI (`client:idle` > `client:visible` > `client:load`)
- Always `getCollection('skills')` / `getEntry` — never `fs` for markdown
- Layouts: `BaseLayout` → `DocsLayout` (docs) or `MarketingLayout` (marketing pages)

## CSS

- Design tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css` as CSS custom properties
- Naming: `--{category}-{role}-{modifier?}` (e.g. `--color-fg-default`, `--space-4`)
- Never raw hex/px in components — add a token first
- Component styles in `<style>` blocks (Astro-scoped)
- Dark mode via `data-theme` attribute set before paint (no FOUC)
- Always honor `prefers-reduced-motion`

## Skills data

- `../agent-skills/` is **read-only** — never write to it
- Sync via `bun run sync-skills` (idempotent)
- `src/content/skills/*.md` and `src/data/skills-data.ts` are generated — never hand-edit

## Routing (locked)

Sidebar order: Foundations → Define → Plan → Build → Test → Review → Simplify → Ship

Pages: `/`, `/about`, `/docs`, `/docs/skills/[slug]`, `/404`

Don't add routes or reorder groups without updating SPEC.md.

## Per-skill page contract

1. `<SkillHeaderCard />` — name, description, phase chip, copyable trigger command
2. Rendered SKILL.md body (`.prose` class only)
3. `<RelatedSkills />` — omit if empty

## Dev commands

```bash
bun run check       # lint + typecheck + tests — must pass before done
bun run sync-skills # sync from ../agent-skills/
bun run dev         # http://localhost:4321
bun run test:e2e    # playwright
bun run build       # production
```

## Testing

- Unit tests for all logic in `src/lib/**` and `scripts/sync-skills.ts`
- Playwright for all user-visible flows (SPEC §5)
- TDD for bugs: failing test → fix → green
- `bun run check` must be green — no exceptions

## Prose rules

Voice: warm, plainspoken, developer-honest.

Banned: `seamless`, `robust`, `delve`, `elevate`, `empower`, `leverage`, `unlock`, `supercharge`, `game-changing`, "Let's dive in.", "In today's…", hollow confidence words ("simply", "just"), em-dash overuse.

SKILL.md content is exempt (Addy's words).

## Ask before doing

- New runtime dependency > 5 KB gzipped
- Changing sidebar groups or order
- New top-level route
- Analytics or third-party requests
- Deploying to non-Vercel target
- Push to `main`
- Breaking `skills-data.ts` schema change

## Never do

- Add Tailwind, shadcn, or any UI framework
- Add backend, database, or server-side search
- `git push --force` or skip hooks (`--no-verify`)
- Commit secrets or `.env` files
- Hand-edit synced skill content
- Frame site as official or Anthropic-affiliated
- Replicate impeccable's visual identity (cream / serif / marbled gold)

## Skill invocations

| Situation              | Skill                                                             |
| ---------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Visual work            | `/impeccable craft` (`polish`, `typeset`, `colorize`, `layout`)   |
| UI review before merge | `/web-design-guidelines` + `/code-review`                         |
| Verify UI works        | `/run` then `/verify`                                             |
| Astro patterns         | `.agents/skills/astro/` or `.agents/skills/astro-best-practices/` |
